{
  "texts": [
    "This procedure is repeated until the expression is complete.",
    "Expressions are then evaluated with a reward function R to test the goodness of the fit to the data D for each candidate expression (f) using normalized root-mean-square error,",
    "To generate better expressions (f), the probability distribution p(|) needs to be optimized.",
    "Using a gradient-based approach for optimization requires the reward function R to be differentiable with respect to the RNN parameter, which is not the case.",
    "Instead, the learning objective is defined as the expectation of the reward under expressions from the policy, i.e., J = ∼p(|) [R], and reinforcement learning is used to maximize J by means of the \"standard policy gradient\":"
  ]
}